Package com.bluegosling.collections.immutable Description

Immutable and persistent collections. This package contains abstract base classes that can be used to implement immutable and persistent data structures.

Guava's ImmutableCollection types do not allow sub-typing, explicitly to ensure that they are immutable (e.g. a misbehaved subclass could violate the immutability guarantee). The base types in this package, on the other hand, are intended to be sub-classed to aid implementation of new immutable types.

Also of note: this package contains interfaces for persistent collections, parallel to the normal mutable interfaces in the JCF. Implementations of these interfaces are also provided.
